The paper investigates the impact of three approaches to XML retrieval, which are all related to information retrieval and databases. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases). The paper also mentions the use of a hybrid system that extracts elements from articles, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the analysis of relevance assessments, which could be related to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
